      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHY I'M BROKE (3) lines up chasing another win after sizzling around this track over 300m in 16.56 on March 8. Hot win latest and looks the one to beat again. DINOSAUR DEANO (1) hit the ground running with a scorching early sectional but had to settle for a minor placing when a 3 length second over 350m at this track, clocking 19.39. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and two minor placings from nine starts. Overdue and is among the main hopes. ZELDA BRAGA (8) tends to drift back and work into the race, charging home into the minors two back before winding up late into third (28.28) in a Grade 4/5 at Bendigo last time. Solid winning record at this trip. Comes through a solid form race last start. Hard to beat again. SON OF WITCHY (7) jumps at a shorter trip and still warrants respect.",
